Name: R0 Reproduction Number
Notes: Infections the first case can be expected to generate (see Dictionary)

Name: External Infections per Day
Notes: Size of external infection events

Name: Superspreader Event Date
Notes: Day on which a superspreader event occurs (if any)

Name: Superspreader Event Size
Notes: Size of superspreader event(if any)

Name: Test Sensitivity (%)
Notes: Chance of detecting Covid if there is Covid

Name: Test Specificity (%)
Notes: Chance of detecting no Covid if there is no Covid

Name: Testing Cadence
Notes: Interval between tests

Name: Confirmatory Test Cost ($)
Notes: Currently assuming 100% sens/spec

Name: False Positive Release Time
Notes: Days for False Positive to be released
textAdd: day(s) to screen out false positives

Name: Average Size of Shared Housing
Notes: Number of Students Living Together

Name: Probability of Roommate Infection
Notes: Chance one infected pod member infects another

Name: Frequency of Social Gatherings
Notes: Days between parties

Name: Number of Students attending Social Gatherings
Notes: Size of parties

Name: Number of Contacts at Social Gatherings
Notes: Contacts per student per party

Name: Probability of Infection Given Contact
textAdd: probability of infection conditional on contact

Name: Recovery Time (days)
Notes: Days to recover from illness

Name: Incubation Time (days)
Notes: Time between getting infected & being infectious

Name: Conditional Mortality
Notes: Chance of death if hospitalized (for student age group)

Name: Proportion Developing Symptoms
Notes: Chance of symptoms developing if infected

Name: Community Transmission Rate (Days)
Notes: Days between external infection events

Name: Test-Isolation Delay (Hours)

Name: Days before first round of isolations
textAdd: day(s) before the first round of isolation

Name: Max Contacts Traced
Notes: Number of Contacts Traceable in a day

Name: Contact Tracing Accuracy
Notes: Proportion of contacts that are accurately reported

Name: Contact Tracing Window
Notes: How many days to contact trace
textAdd: days to look back for CT

Name: Contact Tracing Delay
Notes: How many days to get CT results

Name: Contact Tracing Response Rate
Notes: What % of people respond to CT

Name: Quarantine Time
Notes: Time spent in quarantine if contact traced

Name: Contact Tracing (1 if True)
Notes: Is contact tracing being conducted?

Name: Serology Test (1 if true)
Notes: Has the Serology Test been administered?

Name: Pooled Test (1 if true)
Notes: Are PCR tests being conducted by pod?

Name: Parties (1 if true)
